  "prompt": "What do you say to the man you love when it's over?",
  "response": "When a relationship ends, expressing your feelings honestly and respectfully can help both you and your partner move forward. Here's a gentle and compassionate way to communicate when it's over:\n\n---\n\n\"[His Name], I've spent a lot of time thinking about us and our relationship, and it's with a heavy heart that I need to share something important with you. I've come to realize that we need to go our separate ways. \n\nThis decision hasn't been easy for me, as I truly love you and cherish the time we've spent together. You've brought so much joy and love into my life, and for that, I'll always be grateful. However, I believe that moving forward separately is the best path for both of us.\n\nI want you to know that my feelings for you are real, and this decision is not a reflection of those feelings diminishing. It's about recognizing what's best for our individual growth and happiness. \n\nI hope we can both find peace and fulfillment in the future. You deserve all the happiness in the world, and I truly wish that for you.\n\nThank you for everything, and please take care.\"\n\n---\n\nThis message conveys your love, acknowledges the difficulty of the situation, and expresses your hope for both of your futures. Adjust the wording as needed to fit your personal circumstances and feelings.",
